The two Marines who were killed after their helicopter crashed during a military training exercise on Friday have been named.

Captain Elizabeth Kealey and First Lieutenant Adam Satterfield died from their injuries in the crash  at the Twentynine Palms Marine base in Southern California.

They were traveling in a Third Marine Aircraft Wing chopper when it went down at the Marine Corps Air Ground Combat Center in Twentynine Palms on Friday afternoon.

