He said: 'Our hearts go out to the families and friends of the Marines we lost in this tragic accident.'

He added there was no immediate word on a cause of the crash, which occurred around 4.30pm.

According to its website, the Combat Center's mission 'is to conduct relevant live-fire combined arms training, urban operations, and Joint/Coalition level integration training' for Marines and Navy sailors. 

It is situated in San Bernardino County, about 130 miles east of Los Angeles. 

 

